President Trump's National Security Advisor, Michael T. Flynn, has announced several additions to the National Security Council senior staff. These additions have diverse backgrounds in business, law, technology, government, the military, and the Intelligence community. 

David Cattler will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President for Regional Affairs, overseeing and coordinating the NSC staff's regional senior directors and global security policy development and evaluation. He has over 20 years of experience in leadership positions in the Intelligence Community and Department of Defense.

John Eisenberg will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President, NSC Legal Advisor, and Deputy Counsel to the President for National Security Affairs. He previously served as a senior national-security official at the Department of Justice and has expertise in complex national-security matters.

Kevin Harrington will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President for Strategic Planning. He was previously a managing director and head of research for Thiel Macro LLC, a global macro hedge fund. He also has experience consulting on foreign policy and conducting mathematics research for the Department of Defense.

Kenneth I. Juster will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President for International Economic Affairs. He will coordinate the Administration's international economic policy and act as the President's representative for various summits. Juster has extensive experience in both the public and private sectors, including serving as Under Secretary of Commerce and as a Partner at the investment firm Warburg Pincus.

Overall, these additions bring a wealth of experience and fresh ideas to the National Security Council senior staff.